    When we started looking for a day care for our daughter, our main concern was to find someone who can help her develop good eating habits with patience. It turned out to be very tough for us as we tried couple of day cares before choosing love and laughter day care. Love and laughter day care has been a good choice for my daughter as she has learnt to walk, eat by herself and many other important development milestones over there. My daughter started when she was 12 months old and it's been 4 months so far. Ms Nita and her staff are excellent in terms of giving attention to every kid's needs. Food is home made and they try to feed the kids on demand apart from set schedule. My daughter started learning rhymes and repeats in her own interpretation to our amusement!

    The list goes on but more importantly we would definitely recommend the daycare to any family who is looking for a reliable and safe environment for the children.
